  "case_id": "v4_8die_3d_stack",
  "description": "v4 8-die 3D stack benchmark designed to stress-test TAP bottleneck. 8 dies with 8 FPP lanes shared only among 4 FPP-capable dies (die0, die2, die4, die6). Die1, die3, die5, die7 use serial TAP only. 5 per-die BIST engines, 2 IJTAG instruments. Deep stack with mixed FPP availability creates heavy scheduling tension.",
  "provenance_notes": [
    "v4 task model: test_objects declare mandatory test_types and transport_options.",
    "FPP per-die: only even-layer dies (die0, die2, die4, die6) have FPP. Odd-layer dies (die1, die3, die5, die7) use serial TAP only.",
    "8 FPP lanes are shared among 4 FPP-capable dies -- further FPP pressure.",
    "Deeper stack (8 layers) amplifies TAP bottleneck: each far-die access requires more bypass/select bits.",
    "STAP bypass bits accumulate: accessing die7 requires traversing STAPs on die1..die6 in bypass mode.",
    "5 per-die BIST engines distributed across the stack (die0, die1, die3, die5, die7).",
    "Multiple BIST engines mean many TAP config requests competing for the single serial chain.",
    "2 IJTAG instruments for additional serial-only access tasks.",
    "8 interconnects (adjacent layers), each requiring EXTEST with both dies' DWR segments.",
    "Thermal RC parameters escalate with stack depth; top dies (die6, die7) have worse cooling.",
    "This case demonstrates why scheduling matters: without intelligent interleaving, total test time explodes."
  ],
